properties.description: The following arguments are supported:

properties.name: source
properties.description: • source - (Required) The source exchange.

properties.name: vhost
properties.description: • vhost - (Required) The vhost to create the resource in.

properties.name: destination
properties.description: • destination - (Required) The destination queue or exchange.

properties.name: destination_type
properties.description: • destination_type - (Required) The type of destination (queue or exchange).

properties.name: routing_key
properties.description: • routing_key - (Optional) A routing key for the binding.

properties.name: arguments
properties.description: • arguments - (Optional) Additional key/value arguments for the binding.
The following arguments are supported:

properties.name: name
properties.description: • name - (Required) The name of the exchange.

properties.name: vhost
properties.description: • vhost - (Required) The vhost to create the resource in.

properties.name: settings
properties.description: • settings - (Required) The settings of the exchange. The structure is described below.
The settings block supports:

properties.name: type
properties.description: • type - (Required) The type of exchange.

properties.name: durable
properties.description: • durable - (Optional) Whether the exchange survives server restarts. Defaults to false.

properties.name: auto_delete
properties.description: • auto_delete - (Optional) Whether the exchange will self-delete when all queues have finished using it.

properties.name: arguments
properties.description: • arguments - (Optional) Additional key/value settings for the exchange.
The following arguments are supported:

properties.name: user
properties.description: • user - (Required) The user to apply the permissions to.

properties.name: vhost
properties.description: • vhost - (Required) The vhost to create the resource in.

properties.name: permissions
properties.description: • permissions - (Required) The settings of the permissions. The structure is described below.
The permissions block supports:

properties.name: configure
properties.description: (Required) The "configure" ACL.

properties.name: write
properties.description: (Required) The "write" ACL.

properties.name: read
properties.description: (Required) The "read" ACL.
The following arguments are supported:

properties.name: name
properties.description: • name - (Required) The name of the policy.

properties.name: vhost
properties.description: • vhost - (Required) The vhost to create the resource in.

properties.name: policy
properties.description: • policy - (Required) The settings of the policy. The structure is described below.
The policy block supports:

properties.name: pattern
properties.description: (Required) A pattern to match an exchange or queue name.

properties.name: priority
properties.description: (Required) The policy with the greater priority is applied first.

properties.name: apply_to
properties.description: (Required) Can either be "exchanges", "queues", or "all".

properties.name: definition
properties.description: (Required) Key/value pairs of the policy definition. See the RabbitMQ documentation for definition references and examples.
The following arguments are supported:

properties.name: name
properties.description: • name - (Required) The name of the queue.

properties.name: vhost
properties.description: • vhost - (Required) The vhost to create the resource in.

properties.name: settings
properties.description: • settings - (Required) The settings of the queue. The structure is described below.
The settings block supports:

properties.name: durable
properties.description: • durable - (Optional) Whether the queue survives server restarts. Defaults to false.

properties.name: auto_delete
properties.description: • auto_delete - (Optional) Whether the queue will self-delete when all consumers have unsubscribed.

properties.name: arguments
properties.description: • arguments - (Optional) Additional key/value settings for the queue. All values will be sent to RabbitMQ as a string. If you require non-string values, use arguments_json.

properties.name: arguments_json
properties.description: • arguments_json - (Optional) A nested JSON string which contains additional settings for the queue. This is useful for when the arguments contain non-string values.
The following arguments are supported:

properties.name: name
properties.description: • name - (Required) The name of the user.

properties.name: password
properties.description: • password - (Required) The password of the user. The value of this argument is plain-text so make sure to secure where this is defined.

properties.name: tags
properties.description: • tags - (Optional) Which permission model to apply to the user. Valid options are: management, policymaker, monitoring, and administrator.
The following arguments are supported:

properties.name: name
properties.description: (Required) The name of the vhost.
